The course is divided into two parts: Text Analysis (30 hours) and Grammar (30 hours). In addition, the students are expected to do independent work (96 hours in total). The main focus of Text Analysis is on enhancing students' vocabulary (collocations, connotations, register, word derivation, idioms and expressions) in order to advance their skills at expressing thoughts and exchanging ideas. The Grammar part covers the practical and theoretical aspects of English syntax and morphology. Through extensive language practice the major grammar areas will be covered. The first part of the course focuses on parts of speech, constructions after verbs, real and unreal tenses use, conditionals, passives, inversion, gerund and infinitive, modal verbs, adjectives and adverbs. The course lasts for two semesters. Only students who receive 51% of the possible points at the grammar and vocabulary test are admitted to the English as a minor programme.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Practical English language course for students who wish to minor in English. The aim of the course is to improve students' competence in written and oral communication in English as well as to enhance their vocabulary and grammar. The backbone of the course is language practice; in addition, students are expected to learn the theoretical notions necessary for linguistic discussion and analysis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On successful completion of the course, students will be able to: - form grammatically correct language structures within the scope of the topics covered during the course - explain the use of these structures by referring to the corresponding rule - analyse the use of these structures using the appropriate terminology
